<subSubSection pageId="78" pageNumber="79" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="78.[151,1436,151,320]" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,261,284]" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">Etymology.</emphasis>
The Porcellaneous 
<taxonomicName box="[559,684,260,285]" class="Gastropoda" family="Drilliidae" genus="Cerodrillia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[559,684,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">Cerodrillia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The 
<taxonomicName box="[752,819,260,285]" class="Gastropoda" family="Drilliidae" genus="Clathrodrillia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neogastropoda" pageId="78" pageNumber="79" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="minor">minor</taxonomicName>
epithet is from the Neo-Latin 
<emphasis box="[1168,1299,260,285]" italics="true" pageId="78" pageNumber="79">porcellanus</emphasis>
meaning of porcelain. The shell color and glossy surface are reminiscent of pure white bone china.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
